unction", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` library in R.\\n2. Define the file paths for the input bismark coverage files.\\n3. Use the `methRead` function from `methylKit` to load the methylation data with the specified parameters.\\n4. Save the resulting `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n5. Ensure the file paths are relative and no additional files are generated.\\n6. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (436 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_mWUinDM8QGZ73mDAv6uc4Nex"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ETtLtQzvTsLTOpuTuhurgmMZ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile_paths <- c(\\\"input/sampleA.bismark.cov\\\", \\n                \\\"input/sampleB.bismark.cov\\\", \\n                \\\"input/sampleC.bismark.cov\\\")\\n\\n# Load methylation data\\nmethyl_data <- methRead(file_paths,\\n                        pipeline = \\\"bismarkCoverage\\\",\\n                        mincov = 4,\\n                        treatment = c(0, 0, 0),\\n                        assembly = \\\"mock_v1\\\")\\n\\n# Save the methylRawList object\\nsaveRDS(methyl_data, file = \\\"output/mk_raw.rds\\\")\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var,