/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_mWUinDM8QGZ73mDAv6uc4Nex", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` library in R.\\n2. Define the file paths for the input bismark coverage files.\\n3. Use the `methRead` function from `methylKit` to load the methylation data with the specified parameters.\\n4. Save the resulting `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n5. Ensure the file paths are relative and no additional files are generated.\\n6. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (436 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_mWUinDM8QGZ73mDAv6uc4Nex"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ETtLtQzvTsLTOpuTuhurgmMZ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile_paths <- c(\\\"input/sampleA.bismark.cov\\\", \\n                \\\"input/sampleB.bismark.cov\\\", \\n                \\\"input/sampleC.bismark.cov\\\")\\n\\n# Load methylation data\\nmethyl_data <- methRead(file_paths,\\n                        pipeline = \\\"bismarkCoverage\\\",\\n                        mincov = 4,\\n 